\end{array}\right), \quad \lambda_{a}=\left(\begin{array}{lll}
e & a & b \\
a & b & e
\end{array}\right), \quad \text { and } \quad \lambda_{b}=\left(\begin{array}{lll}
e & a & b \\
b & e & a
\end{array}\right)
$$

The table for this representation is just like the original table with $x$ renamed $\lambda_{x}$, as seen in Table 8.20. For example,

