Let us determine $\mathscr{S}_{H}$, that is, those left cosets that are fixed under action by all elements of $H$. Now $x H=h(x H)$ if and only if $H=x^{-1} h x H$, or if and only if $x^{-1} h x \in H$. Thus $x H=h(x H)$ for all $h \in H$ if and only if $x^{-1} h x=x^{-1} h\left(x^{-1}\right)^{-1} \in H$ for all $h \in H$, or if and only if $x^{-1} \in N[H]$ (see the comment before the lemma), or if and only if $x \in N[H]$. Thus the left cosets in $\mathscr{L}_{H}$ are those contained in $N[H]$. The number of such cosets is $(N[H]: H)$, so $\left|\mathscr{D}_{H}\right|=(N[H]: H)$.

